    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <head>No. 452.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Phelps</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-10-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 4, 1883</date>. (Received
                            October 27.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: An order appeared yesterday announcing that
                        Lima would be evacuated on the 20th instant, and Callao, with its
                        custom-house, on the 21st, the Chilians surrendering the two cities to
                        General Iglesias and retiring to neighboring localities.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S. L. PHELPS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
